<h2>Considerations</h2>
<p>
  We use the <code>&lt;footer&gt;</code> element to wrap content, which provides
  a "contentinfo" role to assistive technologies. Only use one per page.
</p>

<p>
  As in the page header, navigation must use a <code>&lt;nav&gt;</code> element
  which provides the "navigation" role to assistive technologies. Give it an
  aria-label like "Footer menu" to differentiate it from other navs on the page.
</p>

